AB The telecom sector is facing great challenges in its New Product
   Development (NPD) as products are getting increasingly complicated and
   customer segments more fragmented. This study uses a benchmark from the
   automotive industry to obtain ideas for improving NPD and requirements
   management in the telecom sector. Toyota was chosen as the benchmark as
   the automotive industry has been a large volume, mature and competitive
   business sector, and Toyota has been successful in streamlining its
   business processes and in meeting customer needs. The study clarifies
   the similarities and the main differences between interviewed telecom
   companies and NPD practices at Toyota.
