SO INTERNATIONAL JOURNAL OF PRODUCTION RESEARCH
LA English
DT Article
DE postponement; organizational structure; capacity planning
ID MASS-CUSTOMIZATION; SUPPLY CHAIN; DEMAND UNCERTAINTY; MANAGEMENT;
   CAPACITY; DESIGN; SALES; CENTRALIZATION; SPECULATION; DIRECTIONS
AB In view of the slow rate of postponement applications, this paper
   attempts to examine postponement strategies from an
   inter-organizational perspective. The paper first reviews the
   literature on different postponement strategies (including logistics
   postponement, production postponement, purchasing postponement, and
   product-development postponement) mainly within the context of the
   supply chain or supply network. Then, two research questions are
   formulated. This is followed by the investigation into the
   inter-organizational structure and capacity planning in postponement
   applications. The paper concludes with some suggestions for further
   research.
